		<h2>GSA ALUMNI</h2><p>If you attended The Glasgow School of Art for three months or more you are automatically eligible to become a member of GSA Alumni. You join over 6,500 former students and graduates of the School and we can assist you in organising reunions and events - helping you to keep in touch with your fellow students across the world.</p><p>The Glasgow School of Art prides itself on the success of its students and alumni and does not want those achievements to go unnoticed. We look forward to sharing in your news and accomplishments and hope that many of you will help us to provide careers advice, placements and mentoring to current students and assist with recruitment - at home and overseas. Our former students are the School's greatest advocates and can, in many ways, make a valuable contribution to their alma mater.</p><p>We will stay in touch with you, keeping you regularly up to date with developments and achievements at the GSA and, through email, our Internet pages and a twice yearly copy of <b>Flow </b>- the magazine of The Glasgow School of Art, we hope you will continue to feel a part of it. You can help us to do this by keeping us up to date with your address and any items of news in which you think we would be interested. </p><p>As a former student of the GSA, you are a part of its future. We look forward to welcoming you back.</p><p>If you wish to know anything about GSA Alumni please feel free to contact Kate Hollands, Development Manager - Alumni &amp; Friends Relations, Marketing &amp; Development Office on <br />+ 44 (0) 141 353 4788 or <a href="mailto:k.hollands@gsa.ac.uk" target="">k.hollands@gsa.ac.uk</a>.</p><p><b>North American Directory</b></p><p>Collated and co-ordinated by a GSA graduate based in New Jersey, the directory provides a focal point for alumni, based in North America, who wish to keep in touch with former students.<br />Any alumnus, previously included in the directory, who may have changed address and would like to revise their entry, or anyone living in Canada and the United States who wishes to be included, should contact <a href="mailto:k.hollands@gsa.ac.uk" target="">Kate Hollands</a>.</p>
	

	

	

	

	

	

	
	
	
	
	


	
	







